    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-11-14T18:07:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-11-14T18:07:00-05:00" n="189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">775.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/11–352:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Ethiopia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d189fn1">This telegram was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_WAE1">Wellons</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BJK1"
                            >Beard</persName> (<gloss target="#t_AF1">AF</gloss>).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-11-14T18:07:00-05:00"
                            >November 14, 1952—6:07 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>268. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> advised informally price list mil
                    equipment (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 353, Nov 3)<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d189fn2">Not printed; it asked if the Department could tell the
                        Embassy when the list of equipment would be ready. (775.5 <gloss
                            target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/11–352)</note> being actively processed and
                    shld be available approx two weeks. Understand certain items required
                    clarification by <gloss target="#t_MA1">MA</gloss>. When completed price list
                    will be presented <gloss target="#t_Ethio1">Ethio</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> here and transmitted simultaneously to
                        <gloss target="#t_MA1">MA</gloss>.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> also advised informally <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> comite has recommended <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                        >JCS</gloss> approve mil training assistance for <gloss target="#t_Ethio1"
                        >Ethio</gloss> army. Favorable action by <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>
                    and formal notification by Defense to State expected next week.</p>
                <p>Utter told <persName corresp="#p_AAA1">Aklilou</persName> progress being made on
                    above matters and <persName corresp="#p_AAA1">Aklilou</persName> probably
                    informed Emperor. If opportune you may confirm foregoing to Emperor emphasizing
                    final action not yet taken by <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_AAA1">Aklilou</persName> and Spencer are not yet ready
                    conclude base agreement. We have impression they are stalling until after
                    discussion Eritrea item concluded in <gloss target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
